    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header" id="headingFour">
        <h5 class="mb-0">
          <button class="accordion-toggle btn btn-link collapsed" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
            SAY NO TO PLASTIC CLING WRAP
          </button>
        </h5>
      </div>
      <div id="collapseFour" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-parent="#challenge-accordion">
        <div class="card-body container">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-2">
              <%= image_tag("saran.jpeg", size: '100x100') %>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-10">
              <div>
                Plastic wrap is often used once and then tossed. It may be thin and can conform to smaller sizes,
                but it's still plastic. Resources went into making it, and it does not biodegrade, so it just sits in landfills,
                intrudes upon natural environments, or fills our oceans. We challenge you to go plastic-free for food
                packaging this week. Store all of your food with reusable containers and cloth/linen napkins.
                In the fridge. For lunch. On the go.
              </div>

              <div class="learn-more">
                <p class="learn-more-header">Learn more</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <a class="learn-more-text" href="http://trashisfortossers.com/how-to-store-your-leafy-greens-to-help/">How to store food in a cloth/linen napkin</a>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <a class="learn-more-text" href="http://trashisfortossers.com/take-out-zero-waste-style/">How to store takeout</a>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <a class="learn-more-text" href="http://trashisfortossers.com/storing-leftovers-waste-free/">How to store leftovers</a>
                  </li>
